instruction: [INST] Analyze this file to learn MacBook motherboard repair. The 'definitions' section explains key technical terms. The 'threads' section contains real-world repair discussions. Use both sections to understand and learn how to troubleshoot MacBook issues. Posts from username 'larossmann' , 'dukefawks' , and '2informaticos' are posts from trusted experts.[/INST]

definitions.820-00134: What is 820-00134? a LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER.
definitions.3V3_S5: What is 3V3_S5? 3V3_S5 and PP3V3_S5 are interchangeable, see definition for PP3V3_S5. .

threads.title: <LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER>820-00134</LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER> - dead, no LEDs
threads.message:
Device dead, no LED lights up.

I tested with another source and nothing. I have <SIGNAL>PP12V_S5</SIGNAL>, but on <TRANSISTOR>Q8470</TRANSISTOR> pin 4 (<SIGNAL>FET_EN_P12V_S5_R</SIGNAL>) has 10v, so I changed <TRANSISTOR>Q8470</TRANSISTOR>, but it didn't change pin 4.

I don't have this new component, I removed it from another identical board.

Any tips to find out if the problem is still the <TRANSISTOR>Q8470</TRANSISTOR>?

threads.title: <LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER>820-00134</LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER> - dead, no LEDs
threads.message:
Don't bothr with <TRANSISTOR>Q8470</TRANSISTOR> if you get stable <SIGNAL>12V_S5_FET</SIGNAL> voltage.

S5 LED (LE0301) must come on.
If not, check <CHIP>U7600</CHIP> voltages; you may need to change it.

BTW, did you test removing CMOS cell?

threads.title: <LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER>820-00134</LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER> - dead, no LEDs
threads.message:
I tested removing the CMOS.

Bad <CHIP>U7600</CHIP> voltages. I'm going to put only the pins that have voltage.

- 4 - 5v
- 5 - 5v
- 6 - 0.3v
- 7 - 0
- 12 - 4v
- 15 - 4.6v
- 17 - 12v
- 18 - 5v
- 24 - 0.5v

I replaced the <CHIP>U7600</CHIP> and the problem continues. No LEDs.

threads.title: <LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER>820-00134</LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER> - dead, no LEDs
threads.message:
Looks like <SIGNAL>3V3_S5</SIGNAL> is enabled, so you should have L7610 voltage.
If not, check all components L/<TRANSISTOR>Q7610</TRANSISTOR> related.

Did you use "C" version for <CHIP>U7600</CHIP>?

threads.title: <LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER>820-00134</LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER> - dead, no LEDs
threads.message: I didn't use it, I didn't have a C version. Do I solve that first?
